File: The Automobile Association expects the petrol price to fall by as much as 27 cents a litre, with diesel lower by around 11 cents. JOHANNESBURG - Motorists can expect a healthy cut in the fuel price next week. This is due to the sharp slump in the oil price and gains in the rand/dollar exchange rate. READ: Are oil prices over the worst of the crisis? The Automobile Association expects the petrol price to fall by as much as 27 cents a litre, with diesel lower by around 11 cents. The petrol price was cut by up to 32c at the beginning of October. New prices kick in on Wednesday next week.